               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">I have two sheets, pawned by a female—these are the two tickets I gave her.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1182" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1182" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1182" type="surname" value="COLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1182" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM COLE</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">shopman to Mr. Savage, pawnbroker, Whitechapel.</hi> I have a sheet, pawned by a woman—I gave her this duplicate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was there three weeks; the last twelve days I was in rather distressing circumstances; I was going out on the Saturday morn<lb></lb>ing, and, when in the street, she called me and told me as I was going to re<lb></lb>ceive money I might make use of a blanket or sheet; I told her I would not do so if it was not requisite, but if I was disappointed I should feel obliged if she would allow me to do so.</p>
